.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2026" "1.0" "Simple Shell"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic shell that reads commands from standard input and executes them.
It supports commands with arguments, searches in PATH, and runs programs
using fork and execve.

.PP
The shell is structured across multiple source files:
.TP
.B shell.c
Handles the main loop, prompt display, input reading, and command parsing.
.TP
.B executor.c
Handles PATH resolution and command execution using fork and execve.
.TP
.B simple_shell.h
Header file containing function prototypes, macros, and shared definitions.

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Print the environment variables.

.SH USAGE
Run the shell:
.PP
.B ./hsh
.PP
Run a command:
.PP
.B ls -l

